cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.CY

This paper discusses the design features and performance implications of distributed ledgers, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR), distributed computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), software engineering (cs.SE), and cryptography (cs.CY). The paper also proposes a taxonomy and classification of distributed ledger systems, which further supports the likelihood of these sub-categories.
